The paper is about insider threat detection, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed model combines temporal point processes and recurrent neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model also captures session durations and intervals, which are related to sequential data analysis and time-series modeling (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions that the model outperforms existing approaches, which suggests that it involves some form of optimization or learning algorithm (cs.NE).
